The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: owner
properties.description: (Required) The owner of this repository. Can be you or any team you have write access to.

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The name of the repository.

properties.name: slug
properties.description: (Optional) The slug of the repository.

properties.name: scm
properties.description: (Optional) What SCM you want to use. Valid options are hg or git. Defaults to git.

properties.name: is_private
properties.description: (Optional) If this should be private or not. Defaults to true.

properties.name: website
properties.description: (Optional) URL of website associated with this repository.

properties.name: language
properties.description: (Optional) What the language of this repository should be.

properties.name: has_issues
properties.description: (Optional) If this should have issues turned on or not.

properties.name: has_wiki
properties.description: (Optional) If this should have wiki turned on or not.

properties.name: project_key
properties.description: (Optional) If you want to have this repo associated with a project.

properties.name: fork_policy
properties.description: (Optional) What the fork policy should be. Defaults to allow_forks.

properties.name: description
properties.description: (Optional) What the description of the repo is.
